Here we will set up the **Input** (Game Controls) to control the character and create a **Game Mode** which will use our character. 

1.	**Right-click** in the **Content Browser** and create a new **Blueprint Class** of the **Game Mode** class and name it **MyGame**. 

1.	Open the **MyGame** Blueprint, then click the **Class Defaults** button from the toolbar. 

	![](SelectClassDefaults.png)

1.	In the **Details** panel under **Classes**, set the **Default Pawn Class** to use the **MyCharacter** Blueprint. 

	![](GameMode_1.png)

1.	**Compile** and **Save** then close the Blueprint. 

1.	From the Main Editor Window, click **Edit** from the **Menu Bar** and select **Project Settings**. 

1.	In Project Settings, click **Input** under the **Engine** section. 

1.	Under **Bindings**, add four **Action Mappings** and four **Axis Mappings**.

1.	For the first two **Axis Mappings**, click the plus sign next to each one to add an additional mapping to the group. 

	![](Input_1.png)(w:480)

	Your empty Bindings should look like above. 

1.	Set up your **Bindings** similar to below (make sure to set the **Scale** for **A**, **S**, and **Mouse Y** to **-1.0**). 

	![](Input_2.png)(w:480)

	Here we set inputs for **Jump**, **Crouch**, **Jog**, and **Prone** for the **Action Mappings** and **MoveForward**, **MoveRight**, **Turn**, and **LookUp** for the **Axis Mappings**. You can set these as shown or select your own inputs for each. 

	[REGION:note]
	For more details on this process, see [](Gameplay\HowTo\SetUpInput\Blueprints) for more information. 
	[/REGION]

1.	Click the **Maps & Modes** option under the **Project** section of Project Settings. 

1.	In Maps & Modes under **Default Modes**, set the **Default GameMode** to use the **MyGame** Game Mode. 

	![](GameMode_2.png)

	[REGION:note]
	For more details on Game Modes, see [](Gameplay\HowTo\SettingUpAGameMode) for more information. 
	[/REGION]

1.	After setting both the Input and Game Mode settings, close the Project Settings Window. 

